<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Herrick</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 509.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your telegram of December
                            27, 3 p.m., and my despatch No. 494 of January 2, 1914, in regard to the
                            arrest of Mr. Joseph Nouguier, for non-performance of his military
                            service, I have the honor to report that in accordance with your
                            telegraphic instructions of January 16, 2 p.m., I have presented his
                            case to the Foreign Office and requested that it be made possible for
                            him to leave France and return to America.</p>
                        <p>I will cable the Department the result of my representations as soon as
                            an answer is received from the Foreign Office.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Myron T. Herrick</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>